adjective.description: No longer produced or used; out of date.
examples: the disposal of old and obsolete machinery

adjective.description: (of a part or characteristic of an organism) less developed than formerly or in a related species; rudimentary; vestigial.

verb.description: Cause (a product or idea) to be or become obsolete by replacing it with something new.
examples: we're trying to stimulate the business by obsoleting last year's designs

origin: Late 16th century: from Latin obsoletus grown old, worn out, past participle of obsolescere fall into disuse.
